previewArticle.title: Columbus Crew vs. FC Dallas | MLS Match Preview

recapArticle.title: Columbus Crew 0, FC Dallas 0 | MLS Match Recap

timelineItems.desc: The Columbus Crew and FC Dallas resume their league activity following the World Cup break as the clubs meet in an interconference matchup after a weather delay at Crew Stadium.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: Columbus Crew vs FC Dallas | June 29, 2014

timelineItems.comment: First Half begins.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: And we're off. The rain has stopped as well. I think we'll get the full game in tonight. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 1': Here we go! @FCDallas kicks off, #Crew96 attacking toward the Nordecke in the first half.

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: Trapp once again involved in the attack. Getting forward to deliver a cross there that is cleared by #FCDallas. We saw some of this Wed.

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: In his first game back after missing three with a knee injury. Wil Trapp wearing some black tape on the outside of his right knee. #crew96

timelineItems.desc: Attempt blocked. Michel (FC Dallas) left footed shot from the center of the box is blocked.
timelineItems.title: BLOCK: Michael Parkhurst stands firm on the line to deny Michel

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 10 minutes in and #Crew96 have had the better of the play so far. Only clear cut chance has gone to Jimenez but Crew controlling.

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Michel (FC Dallas) left footed shot from outside the box is high and wide to the right. Assisted by Je-Vaughn Watson with a cross.
Attempt blocked. Michel (FC Dallas) left footed shot from the centre of the box is blocked.
Offside, FC Dallas. Victor Ulloa tries a through ball, but Andrés Escobar is caught offside.

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: So here this comes... #Crew96 http://t.co/3Zyw9TDfbx

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: So here this comes... #Crew96 http://t.co/3Zyw9TDfbx

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Michael Parkhurst may have just made the #MLS save of the week. Clark was out of net. Incredible. #Crew96

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Justin Meram (Columbus Crew) right footed shot from long range on the left is close, but misses to the right
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Justin Meram curls a shot just outside the post

timelineItems.comment: Offside, Columbus Crew. Ben Speas tries a through ball, but Jairo Arrieta is caught offside.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 13': CHANCE - FCD long throw leads to a bouncing ball in the box, and Michael Parkhurst makes a spectacular goal-line save for #Crew96.

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Justin Meram (Columbus Crew) right footed shot from the left side of the box is close, but misses to the right. Assisted by Ben Speas.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 14' Speas slows pace after streaking thru #FCDallas mids to allow backline to catch up for pass to Arrieta, latter still way #offside. #MLS

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 15': CHANCE - Justin Meram nearly duplicates his match-winner in Seattle. A curler from the left side drifts just wide of the post. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: When teams let Justin Meram cut to his right and set up for a curler, they're giving him exactly what he wants. Nearly capitalized there.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Speas has been very solid today so far. With the way the game has been going so far he will probably end up with an assist. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: Roughly 60% possession for #Crew96 in the early going. In other words, a nearly-typical day at the office so far.

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: 15’ CLOSE from Meram! Cuts in from the left and tries to curl one to the far post. Inches wide. Seitz missed it too. #Crew96 #DTID

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 17' Gehrig establishing backline presence once again. In position to deny #FCDallas another legitimate SOG. Still 0-0 here in #CLB.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Rain now coming down and somehow in sideways with how hard this wind is blowing. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 18' Aaaand here comes the rain again. Fans start to scatter to concourse. #Nordecke not budging, still cheering loud and proud. #MLS #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Some fans make their way for the stadium overhangs, but the nordecke hasn't budged. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: Here comes the rain and there goes the crowd. Now we will see the best #Crew96 soccer of the season.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 20' Barson not letting Escobar get away with anything along left side. #FCDallas throw-in to Michel, resetting possession in own half. #MLS

timelineItems.comment: Match ends, Columbus Crew 0, FC Dallas 0.

timelineItems.desc: The Columbus Crew and FC Dallas resume their league activity following the World Cup break as the clubs meet in an interconference matchup after a weather delay at Crew Stadium.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Columbus Crew vs FC Dallas | June 29, 2014

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: #CLBvDAL end in a scoreless draw. Akindele will want this one back: http://t.co/i1bBVwlqyY http://t.co/Lca1wA52wH

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: #CLBvDAL end in a scoreless draw. Akindele will want this one back: http://t.co/i1bBVwlqyY http://t.co/Lca1wA52wH

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Andrés Escobar (FC Dallas) right footed shot from outside the box is too high. Assisted by Tesho Akindele.
Attempt blocked. Ben Speas (Columbus Crew) right footed shot from outside the box is blocked. Assisted by Jairo Arrieta.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 21': Arrieta makes a nice on-ball run through the defense before laying off to Speas. His shot is deflected out for a corner. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Gehrig was barreling in to head that corner, but #FCDallas had him marked perfectly. #Crew96 still scoreless

timelineItems.comment: Corner,  Columbus Crew. Conceded by Adam Moffat.

timelineItems.name: Joe Grish
timelineItems.text: Both Head Coaches from #Crew96 and are wearing red ribbons today in support of Stu Tudor. http://t.co/xFdETV2bMY

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: ...And just like that, it seems that the rain has blown over. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 22': Michel finds Akindele in the box with a nice cross, but the FCD attacker can't bring it down cleanly. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Now the sun is out shining bright like nothing ever happened. Don't play me like that sun, I know it was just raining. I'm not dumb. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 fans head on back to your seats. Rain has stopped... for now.

timelineItems.name: Keep D.C. United
timelineItems.text: Our thoughts are with @ColumbusCrew fan and Columbus Fire Lieutenant Stu Tudor, his family, and the whole #Crew96 family. #MLS

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 22' #FCDallas takes shot on goal after some jam-up defense, sails high. Get another possession moments later, Barson w/ physical slide tkl.

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Tesho Akindele (FC Dallas) right footed shot from the left side of the box misses to the left. Assisted by Je-Vaughn Watson.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 23' #FCDallas seems resolute to step up tempo of this match suddenly. Using whole field to set up scheme before surging forward. #CLBvsDAL

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 counter attacking quite a bit but only doing so with four usually. Jimenez, Speas, Arrieta, and Meram. Need more numbers forward.

timelineItems.desc: Attempt missed. Bernardo Anor (Columbus Crew) left footed shot from outside the box is close, but misses to the right. Assisted by Chad Barson wi
timelineItems.title: CHANCE: Bernardo Anor tries a volley from distance

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Bernardo Anor (Columbus Crew) left footed shot from outside the box is close, but misses to the right. Assisted by Chad Barson with a cross.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Anor takes a beautiful strike that was just inches wide after the throw in. #Crew96 #FCDallas 0-0 27'

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Bernardo Anor struck that volley perfectly, but it sails just wide. Could've been an incredible goal. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: FC Dallas
timelineItems.text: JUST WIDE: Anor rips one on the volley from outside the box and he misses by a foot. Still 0-0 in the 27th min. #DTID #CLBvFCD

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 26': CHANCE - Anor hits a first-time volley from just outside the box, but the shot drifts just wide of the right post. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 26' Jimenez cross from the right finds Anor at the top of the 18-yard box. His volley narrowly misses giving #Crew96 the lead

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: 26’ CLOSE this time from Anor off the volley. Would have been an absolutely incredible goal if that went in. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Jimenez has been making dangerous runs from the right wing the entire game and his teammates continue to miss him. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Jimenez tries to run down the ball, but Benitez shields it nicely for a #FCDallas goal kick. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 28' Trapp with a good effort to dissect backline with assist attempt to Jimenez but #FCDallas' Benitez beats him to it. #GoalKick upcoming.

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Adam Moffat (FC Dallas).
Tony Tchani (Columbus Crew) wins a free kick in the defensive half.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: We're gonna need some squeegees. #Crew96 Maybe a shamwow.

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: With Barson/Anor as the fullbacks, this is a very unbalanced 4-2-3-1 from #Crew96. Anor is much higher and wider.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: As we kick-off today’s match, the #Crew96 family would like to extend our thoughts and prayers to Columbus Fire’s Lt. Stu Tudor.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: The Trapp-Jimenez relationship is looking like it'll prove dangerously effective for #Crew96 if they can find looks in transition. #CLBvsDAL

timelineItems.name: Aaron Helbert
timelineItems.text: This just in, #Crew96 forward Jairo Arrieta moves slightly faster than a trot as he watches the ball skip away. #workhardplayhard

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 31' Jimenez doing a good job defensively too; he and Barson are terrorizing #FCDallas on the left side of the visitors' attacking 1/2. #MLS

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Benitez totally lifted his back foot on that throw-in. Just sayin. #FCDallas #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: Arrieta and Jimenez definitely communicating to coordinate something. The desire for shots on goal is apparent in body language. #Crew96

timelineItems.comment: Jair Benitez (FC Dallas) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Foul by Héctor Jiménez (Columbus Crew).

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Speas and Tchani have a bit of confusion over who will play the ball at the top of the box, and #Crew96 never get a good play out of it.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: Right on cue, 33' pass attempted by Jimenez to Arrieta, deflected by #FCDallas. Benitez dispossesses Jimenez moments later. #CLBvsDAL

timelineItems.comment: Justin Meram (Columbus Crew) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Foul by Zach Loyd (FC Dallas).
Wil Trapp (Columbus Crew) wins a free kick in the attacking half.
Foul by Michel (FC Dallas).

timelineItems.name: Paul Garlock
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 attack is horrid. Tchani didn't bring a brain today. Anor just hanging on the wing waiting to pounce instead of doing ANY work.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 35': Trapp gets forward and draws a foul on Michel. Speas sends the free kick into the box, but FCD clears. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Trapp is tripped by Michel on what would've been a great run. A little surprised the yellow didn't come out. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: That's two chances for #FCDallas in as many minutes. They're getting their attacking together a bit in the 38' #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 38': Loyd sends a cross in toward Akindele, but he's blanketed by Barson and Gehrig as the ball goes through the box. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 37' Akindele looks like he's going to get a shot, Crew backline repels his effort. Still scoreless here in #CLB. #MLS #Crew96 #FCDallas

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 38' Loyd sends a dangerous ball into the #Crew96 penalty area. Akindele looks to get his head on it but Barson does a good job to defend.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Speas brought down by Loyd about 5 yards away from the box, but ref with a no-call. I'm a bit surprised, even after seeing replay. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Gregg Berhalter pantomiming Ben Speas getting taken down from behind is my highlight of the match. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Fans are crammed into the concourse, and I hear the Nordecke in full voice right now. #crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 official twitter sending their thoughts and prayers to Stu Tudor as the game begins.

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Wil Trapp just looked very timid in his first post-knee-injury tackle. I'm sure he doesn't quite trust it yet. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 2' Action clustering around midfield so far. 2 consecutive #FCDallas throw-ins within seconds. Clear by #Crew96 GK Clark. #CLBvsDAL #MLS

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Wil Trapp hasn't been bad by any means, but he's showing some rust. Getting up slowly, tackling gingerly. He's not himself yet. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Greg Grant
timelineItems.text: Pretty awful missed call against #crew96 costs team a prime scoring opportunity #blindsided #typicalMLSrefereeing

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Tesho Akindele (FC Dallas).
Chad Barson (Columbus Crew) wins a free kick on the right wing.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 40' #FCDallas don't seem in sync with regard to the service/assist game. Individual talent, but they're not meshing in the attacking 1/3.

timelineItems.comment: Tesho Akindele (FC Dallas) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Foul by Eric Gehrig (Columbus Crew).

timelineItems.name: Paul Garlock
timelineItems.text: Anor gassed already? Wondering why GB camps him out there. He provides nothing when he has two FCD defenders between him and the 18 #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Anor has been excellent thus far. He always seems coiled and ready to spring. He looks sharp. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 42' Free kick after #Crew96 foul on Akindele. Jimenez and Arrieta moving with a purpose to contest in midfield. #CLBvsDAL #Crew96 #MLS

timelineItems.comment: Attempt saved. Héctor Jiménez (Columbus Crew) left footed shot from outside the box is saved in the bottom right corner. Assisted by Wil Trapp.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Anor did a good job to get that deflection back into #Crew96 possession.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: 45' now, I don't think there will be much stoppage time. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Erik Bobbitt
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 really pushing numbers forward, especially with Anor at LB acting like a LM. It's really fun to watch, actually.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 44': Jimenez wiggles into some space at the top of the box, but his curling attempt is easily caught by Seitz. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: 44' Jimenez has the ball at the top of the #FCDallas penalty area. Has no passing outlets so sends a chip shot in. Easy catch for Seitz.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: About 5 seconds of stoppage time, so #Crew96 and #FCDallas go into the half scoreless. Both teams have had chances, 2nd half should be good

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Not an incredibly interesting first half. Some MLS matches have been off to the races this weekend after the break. Not this one. #Crew96

timelineItems.comment: First Half ends, Columbus Crew 0, FC Dallas 0.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: HALFTIME: #Crew96 0 - @FCDallas 0 Black & Gold head into the break scoreless with Dallas.

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Halftime: #Crew96 0, #FCDallas 0: Pretty boring first half. Crew passing well but I think the conditions are playing against both teams.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 had 83% passing accuracy in the 1st half, and 56.9% possession.

timelineItems.name: FC Dallas
timelineItems.text: HALF: @FCDallas 0, @ColumbusCrew 0 - @Seitzy1 with the clean sheet in the first half and he head to the break goalless. #DTID #CLBvFCD

timelineItems.name: Ben Hickey
timelineItems.text: Slow pace to that first half, the heat and Open Cup games in midweek are probably catching up with both sides. #CLBvDAL

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: First half thoughts: Arrieta is very active. Barson looks better on the right than left. #Crew96 need more numbers in attacks.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: No stoppage time in relatively crisp and clean 1st half. Still 0-0 here in Columbus. #Crew96 attacking & playing efficiently. #CLBvsDAL

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: #FCDallas had to make 15 clearances, compared to just 4 for #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Keros Lowder
timelineItems.text: After that boring World Cup match this morning, I'm glad we get this barn burner in Columbus!! #CLBvDAL #Zzzz

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 stats: 56.9% of possession, 254 passes completed on an 83% success rate, 5 shots with 2 on target.

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: After 45' - Good: Speas, Anor, Jimenez. Arrieta has been fairly quiet. Barson at RB is more solid for back four. Trapp is rusty. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Justin Meram hasn't been bad. But every good #Crew96 chance has come from quick linking play. That's not his game. Wants to dribble/shoot.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 looking efficient. Speas, Anor've been very good, Trapp's been OK but not on usual level, Arrieta adjusted after early miscues. #MLS

timelineItems.name: Dustin Grovemiller
timelineItems.text: That concessions run timed exactly with the sudden downpour. So I've got that going for me. Which is nice. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: Tony Tchani has the most touches for #Crew96 with 47. 1 ahead of Anor and Trapp. Completing 92% of his passes.

timelineItems.name: Greg Benson
timelineItems.text: Nordecke have introduced the #Crewvuzela, essentially a continuous buzzing noise yelled as one when the away team has possession. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: B. Norton
timelineItems.text: Sounds like @ColumbusCrew need a little more attacking threat. Bring on Higuain for the second half? #crew96

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: Tony Tchani: 92.1% passing accuracy (35/38) playing mostly in the heart of the field. #Crew96 http://t.co/wQFCV3U7tz

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: HIGHLIGHT: Perfect technique, juuuust wide. http://t.co/MVUmV9gLdA #CLBvDAL #Crew96 http://t.co/vGpS0yROBL

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: Tony Tchani: 92.1% passing accuracy (35/38) playing mostly in the heart of the field. #Crew96 http://t.co/wQFCV3U7tz

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: HIGHLIGHT: Perfect technique, juuuust wide. http://t.co/MVUmV9gLdA #CLBvDAL #Crew96 http://t.co/vGpS0yROBL

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: Also, Chad Barson was 27/28 on passing in the first half (96.43%). #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Brett Zalaski
timelineItems.text: Congrats to @FrankieHejduk2 on his induction into #Crew96 Circle of Honor...he is a legend on the field, & a better person off it. #HatsOff

timelineItems.name: Lefty McClicksalot
timelineItems.text: We are looking a little lethargic in the attacking support... Step it up guys! You're the better team! #DTID @FCDallas

timelineItems.name: FC Dallas
timelineItems.text: We are underway in the second half at Crew Stadium! No changes for either side to start the second half. #DTID #CLBvFCD

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: 46': Arrieta kicks off to Speas and we are off in the second half. Black and Gold, @FCDallas level at 0-0. #Crew96

timelineItems.comment: Second Half begins Columbus Crew 0, FC Dallas 0.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 47' Backline controlling ball and awaiting formations to take shape upfield before distributing ball forward. All #Crew96 so far. #CLBvsDAL

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Meram with a cross to a well covered Arrieta, no real danger for #FCDallas. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 48' Meram switches the field to Jimenez who sends a cross into the #FCDallas box but ti goes just under Arrieta's foot.

timelineItems.name: Cody Sharrett
timelineItems.text: Higuaín is the only #Crew96 sub warming up. I have a feeling his entrance would be very Rick "Wild Thing" Vaughn-esque.

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: Pipa is still warming up exclusively behind the #Crew96 goal. All indications suggest he will come on at some point.

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Je-Vaughn Watson (FC Dallas).
Bernardo Anor (Columbus Crew) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Lineups are announced and players are warming up.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew
timelineItems.text: Both Head Coaches from #Crew96 and @FCDallas are wearing red ribbons today in support of Stu Tudor.

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: #FCDallas are playing a very high line to start this game. Arrieta has already been offside twice though neither has needed to be called.

timelineItems.name: Ryan Schwepfinger
timelineItems.text: Meanwhile, @FCDallas warming up its entire gamut of subs behind the south goal. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Anor seems to be good now. Could've just had the wind knocked out of him momentarily. #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Following weather-related postponement, #CLBvDAL set to kick off at 2pm ET today: http://t.co/axCbl4bUUI http://t.co/74n8WnPGv6

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Following weather-related postponement, #CLBvDAL set to kick off at 2pm ET today: http://t.co/axCbl4bUUI http://t.co/74n8WnPGv6

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 50' Moffat flat out beats Tchani to ball for a clear in midfield. Crew possession reset. #Crew96 #CLBvsDAL #MLS

timelineItems.desc: Tesho Akindele (FC Dallas) hits the right post with a right footed shot from the center of the box.
timelineItems.title: POST: Tesho Akindele clangs a sitter off the post

timelineItems.name: Gina
timelineItems.text: Frankie Hejduk is Shaun White fifteen years from now. #FCDallas #ColumbusCrew

timelineItems.comment: Tesho Akindele (FC Dallas) hits the right post with a right footed shot from the centre of the box. Assisted by Andrés Escobar.

timelineItems.name: jeffrey_r
timelineItems.text: Crew get lucky #crew96

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Andres Escobar just burned most of the #crew96 defense and dished to Tesho Akindele, who somehow missed a point-blank tap-in off the post.

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Escobar absolutely shredded the entire #Crew96 defense there. Dallas really should be leading 1-0. Horrible Akindele miscue.

timelineItems.name: Patrick Murphy
timelineItems.text: #Crew96 dodge a bullet there. Escobar made both Barson and Gehrig look silly on that run. Best chance of the game.

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Escobar took both Gehrig and Parkhurst out of the play there. FC Dallas should be up 1-0. #Crew96 #DTID

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Justin Meram (Columbus Crew).
Andrés Escobar (FC Dallas) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Delay in match Andrés Escobar (FC Dallas) because of an injury.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: Escobar did an amazing job to recover after the Barson tackle, and then just juked Gehrig. #Crew96 really were in a bad spot.

timelineItems.name: Ben Ferree
timelineItems.text: So for those keeping score, Parkhurst and the post have as many saves tonight as Seitz and Clark. #Crew96 #FCDallas

timelineItems.comment: Delay over. They are ready to continue.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
timelineItems.text: 54' Meram w/ challenge on Escobar, he goes down & is shaken up, foul and possession awarded to #FCDallas but no malice, no yellow. #CLBvsDAL

timelineItems.name: Bill Plumley
timelineItems.text: Anyone seeing that mental little bird doing field-level flybys? It was divebombing a lazy hawk earlier #Crew96

timelineItems.name: Andrew Todd-Smith
